
class Solution {
    boolean isValid(char i, char n){
        if(i != n){                   // check if two chars are not equal
            return false;             // return false if mismatch
        }
        return true;                  // return true if chars match
    }

    boolean isPalindrome(String s) {
        int i = 0;                    
        int n = s.length()-1;         // set start (i) and end (n) indices
        
        if(s.charAt(i) != s.charAt(n)) { return false; }  // only checks first and last chars
        
        return isValid(s.charAt(i+1), s.charAt(n-1));    // checks only the second pair
    }
}


////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Palindrome String
You are given a string s. Your task is to determine if the string is a palindrome. A string is considered a palindrome if it reads the same forwards and backwards.

Examples :

Input: s = "abba"
Output: true
Explanation: "abba" reads the same forwards and backwards, so it is a palindrome.

Input: s = "abc" 
Output: false
Explanation: "abc" does not read the same forwards and backwards, so it is not a palindrome.

Constraints:
1 ≤ s.size() ≤ 106

The string s contains only lowercase english letters (a-z).

